<br>
See Hidden<br>
Augmented Dexterity II<br>
Augmented Quickness II<br>
Augmented Constitution I<br>
Mastery of Pain II<br>
Dodger II<br>
Duelist's Reflexes I<br>
Toughness I<br>
Long Wind I<br>
<br>
Aug Con I and Toughness I gave me 22 and 27 hit points, respectively.  Long Wind is a noticable increase in sprint time (or another way to see it, and more relevant to me: a decrease in the Endurance cost to sprint... I almost never sprint out a full Endurance bar).  I plan on getting Mastery of Pain III and Dodger III at R4L4 and R5L0, respectively.<br>
<br>
The only Realm Ability I am somewhat unsatisfied with is, surprisingly (well, not to me), See Hidden.  As expected, archers are adjusting to the change (hiding in trees, travelling with groups, etc.).  However, it is simply too powerful a passive ability to pass up, and I'm sure it will come in handier than it has. <p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valarauco.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugalium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 3:34:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3348.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /respec: the grass IS greener on the other side</span><hr size=1> One question I had is does the increase in weapon attack speed by Mastery of Arms reduce our style damage in the same way an increase of quickness does?<br>
<br>
I agree with you Val on the see hidden thing. For the first few days you saw tons, lately not much. Cant say as I blame them of course.<br>
<br>
Culdor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unandurius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandurius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 4:36:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3348.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /respec: the grass IS greener on the other side</span><hr size=1> Oooh, Mastery of Stealth. Forgot to mention that one.<br>
<br>
I trained it to level 1, and while it's not noticeable when walking alone, it's quite nice when following another stealther -- You can catch up with them without having to unstealth. You can even get ahead of them and line up a perf instead of using BsII. It's quite expensive, I don't know if I'll ever get Level2, but it's one of the more useful skills to have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaedenthestinker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaeden The Stinker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~rogue3d/witch3.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 7:11:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3348.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~rogue3d/witch3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /respec: the grass IS greener on the other side</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, Mastery of Stealth isn't worth the points needed to get it to be of usefullness.<br>
I had MoS up to level 2.  I would race a 50 stealther with 50 stealth.  Think of it like a 50 yard dash, at about 50 yards, I would be about 8 feet in front of him.  Not even a full horse length.  50 Yards running while stealthed was about a 10+ second run.<br>
I wound up respecing, and didn't notice the difference.  The ONLY time I can think this would be of use, is if you spot another assasin, and to get away from them, without unstealthing.  Even then it would take you quite awhile to outdistance them.<br>
On respec, I wound up getting:<br>
See Hidden: Like many have mentioned, not incredibly usefull, because they travel in groups now, but I like knowing where all archers are at all times.  I will keep getting this one.<br>
Viper: I wouldn't get this one again.  To cumbersome to use to be usefull, not to mention the expensive point cost.<br>
Aug Dex 2 for Mastery of Pain 1: This is well worth the point cost, with just only 1 point, I noticed more crits.<br>
I plan to respec again eventually, to drop Viper, I will probably bring MoP up to 3, and get a rain. <p>~Jaeden~ 
<BR>~Nightshade~
<BR>*Smears peanut butter on her face, giggles maniacally, curtsies and vanishes*
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=servo>Servo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 9:13:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3348.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /respec: the grass IS greener on the other side</span><hr size=1> Just a word of caution, Jaed... don't expect too much from Rain :-/ find a local enchanter to give you a dmg add, it'll be much more effective... get about double the extra damage, for ten minutes instead of one, you save 3 points, etc. etc... Do as you may, of course <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaureliuscov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurelius CoV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/02 9:11:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3348.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /respec: the grass IS greener on the other side</span><hr size=1> I think alot of people are overlooking first aid, but its pretty damn sweet. Not usable in combat = you can use it as soon as you stop swinging, even if being beat on. So, for 3 points, a 30% heal that you have to stop swing for, sounds like a pretty good bargain :) and every 15 minutes!!! Wow, thats a great bargain, I might not get 2 but definately FA 1.<br>
<br>
I am not respecing but will definately get it with my next 3 points. It isnt *as* nice because we have less hp than most, but in a close fight it would be worth its weight in gold. <br>
<br>
And when I have jumped someone and they have done this, it scared the @#%$ out of me. Perf, cd, ss poison and some great  hits then blam, he has alot more health and starts swinging. RUN!!!!!!!!! <p><center><br>"I am still learning" <br>
